# Mantine v8 UI Rules

Mantine is the ONLY UI library. No Tailwind. No shadcn. No Radix.

## Components

Use Mantine components exclusively:
- Layout: `Stack`, `Group`, `Box`, `Grid`, `Flex`, `Container`, `SimpleGrid`
- Typography: `Text`, `Title`, `Anchor`, `Highlight`
- Inputs: `TextInput`, `NumberInput`, `Select`, `Textarea`, `FileInput`
- Feedback: `Notification`, `Alert`, `Progress`, `Loader`, `Skeleton`
- Overlay: `Modal`, `Drawer`, `Popover`, `Tooltip`, `Menu`
- Data: `Table`, `Badge`, `Card`, `Timeline`
- File upload: `Dropzone` from `@mantine/dropzone`

## Hooks

Use Mantine hooks instead of building your own:
- `useForm` for form state and validation
- `useDisclosure` for open/close state (modals, drawers)
- `useDebouncedValue` for search inputs
- `useMediaQuery` for responsive logic

## Styling

- NEVER write `className="flex"` or any Tailwind utility class
- Use Mantine's `style` prop for one-off styles
- Use CSS Modules (`*.module.css`) for complex/reusable styles
- Use Mantine's theme tokens for colors, spacing, and typography

## Client Directives

- Add `"use client"` only when the component uses Mantine hooks or browser APIs
- Server Components should remain the default
